---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'
import { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge'
---

<Layout title="About" description="About Jasen Carroll — software engineer with 12 years in FDA-regulated manufacturing.">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">

    <p class="text-xs text-muted tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-wider uppercase mb-12">Jasen Carroll</h1>

    <div class="space-y-12 max-w-2xl">

      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        I'm a software engineer with 12 years in FDA-regulated manufacturing. I build tools for quality teams, compliance programs, and regulated systems — because I've been on the other side of the software those teams depend on.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xs text-muted tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">What I'm Working On</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-l-2 border-border pl-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold mb-1">Specz</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Conversational AI tool that conducts structured product intake interviews and generates comprehensive software specifications. Maps directly to how validation planning works: structured questions, documented outputs, traceable decisions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-2 border-border pl-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold mb-1">Axiomlayer</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Personal AI infrastructure stack on bare metal: Open WebUI, Ollama, n8n workflow automation, Caddy reverse proxy over Tailscale. Self-hosted inference cutting cloud AI costs by 60%+.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-2 border-border pl-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold mb-1">Bun Stack</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Full-stack framework generator for Bun + TypeScript. Rails-inspired conventions, batteries included, one-command Railway deploy.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xs text-muted tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">Background</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            I spent 12 years in FDA-regulated manufacturing — medical devices, pharma combination products, Class II/III. System failures in that world meant 483 observations, warning letters, and product recalls. That shaped how I think about software: understand failure modes, build in observability, design systems that degrade gracefully.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've run CAPA programs under consent decree at Philips, defended EU MDR tech file audits solo at Acumed, written Part 11 compliance tooling, and managed sterilization validation for Class III devices. I've used the QMS software. I know where it falls short.
          </p>
          <p>
            I didn't pivot away from regulated industries — I gained the engineering skills to build better tools for them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xs text-muted tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">Tech Stack</h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          {[
            { label: 'Languages', items: ['TypeScript', 'Python', 'Go', 'SQL'] },
            { label: 'Frontend', items: ['Astro', 'React', 'Svelte', 'Tailwind'] },
            { label: 'Backend', items: ['FastAPI', 'Bun', 'Flask', 'Gin'] },
            { label: 'Data', items: ['PostgreSQL', 'SQLite', 'Drizzle ORM'] },
            { label: 'Infrastructure', items: ['K3s', 'Docker', 'Tailscale', 'Railway'] },
            { label: 'Regulated', items: ['TrackWise', 'MasterControl', 'ETQ', 'Minitab'] },
          ].map(({ label, items }) => (
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
              <span class="text-muted-foreground w-28 shrink-0 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider pt-0.5">{label}</span>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                {items.map(item => <Badge client:load>{item}</Badge>)}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xs text-muted tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">What I'm Looking For</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <p>Software engineering roles at MedTech companies, FDA software vendors, eQMS platforms, or compliance tooling startups. The intersection of deep regulated industry knowledge and software engineering is rare — I bring both.</p>
          <p>Interested in: QMS software, compliance-as-code, regulatory intelligence tooling, validation automation, and anything that makes quality teams more effective.</p>
          <p>Remote preferred. Based in Philadelphia.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xs text-muted tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">Elsewhere</h2>
        <div class="flex gap-6 text-sm">
          <a href="https://github.com/jasencarroll" class="text-muted hover:text-foreground transition-colors tracking-wider">GitHub</a>
          <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/jasenc" class="text-muted hover:text-foreground transition-colors tracking-wider">LinkedIn</a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
